      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental conditions (fluid temperature, hematocrit, shear history) must match COU operating envelope within documented tolerances.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro tests performed at 37°C with bovine blood (hematocrit 35%). COU specifies human blood at physiologic hematocrit 40–45%. Temperature match is adequate; hematocrit deviation introduces unquantified model-form error in Giersiepen coefficients calibrated on bovine data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
