      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoI must be the hemolysis index used in the regulatory submission, not a surrogate scalar.",
      "rationale": "Validation uses the normalized hemolysis index (HI) directly as the QoI, consistent with the regulatory submission metric. Spatial distribution of HI compared at impeller blade passage; volume-averaged HI used for acceptance. Achieved level 3 because local peak HI in blade tip clearance was not separately validated."
    },
